  returns, so `var_1 == 0` and the specified implementation correctly returns
  NaN. The test uses a deterministic increasing series with non-constant
  increments so the positive VR assertion can exercise the formula.
- Claude's exact ADF random-walk text, cumulative sum of all-one increments,
  gives a low p-value under statsmodels `adfuller(..., autolag="AIC")` in this
  environment. The test uses a seeded deterministic random walk from normal
  increments, which gives the intended high p-value check.

